reviews.subject: Introduction to Computer Science
reviews.review: Dr. Carter is amazing at explaining complex concepts in a simple way. Her classes are engaging and her office hours are very helpful.

reviews.subject: Software Engineering
reviews.review: Nguyen is a great teacher who encourages hands-on learning. His projects are fun but can be a bit overwhelming at times.

reviews.subject: Algorithms and Data Structures
reviews.review: Dr. Mitchell is very knowledgeable but her lectures can be a bit dry. Be prepared to put in extra study hours.

reviews.subject: Database Systems
reviews.review: Dr. Patel is thorough and detailed in his lectures. He can be strict, but if you follow along and ask questions, you'll do well.

reviews.subject: Operating Systems
reviews.review: Rossi is a good lecturer with clear explanations. Sometimes the workload can be heavy, but she is supportive.

reviews.subject: Artificial Intelligence
reviews.review: Dr. Thompson is an AI expert and his passion for the subject is clear. He makes difficult concepts much easier to grasp.

reviews.subject: Computer Networks
reviews.review: Dr. Lee's lectures are well-structured and informative. She is very responsive to questions both in class and online.

reviews.subject: Discrete Mathematics
reviews.review: Anderson's lectures can be confusing and disorganized. The exams are tough, and you have to do a lot of self-study.

reviews.subject: Human-Computer Interaction
reviews.review: Dr. Williams is great at making HCI fun and creative. Her feedback is incredibly valuable and helps improve your work.

reviews.subject: Web Development
reviews.review: Brown is laid-back and knowledgeable. The course is hands-on, but sometimes the guidance is a bit lacking.

reviews.subject: Software Design Patterns
reviews.review: Dr. Green's course is very well organized and insightful. She encourages critical thinking and provides great real-world examples.

reviews.subject: Mobile App Development
reviews.review: White's class is okay, but his lectures can be a bit dull. The projects are useful but sometimes lack clear direction.

reviews.subject: Cybersecurity
reviews.review: Dr. Harris is extremely knowledgeable in cybersecurity. Her classes are challenging but rewarding if you put in the effort.

reviews.subject: Data Science
reviews.review: Carter is a good lecturer with a lot of industry experience. Sometimes the material can be a bit dense, but he is helpful.

reviews.subject: Machine Learning
reviews.review: Dr. Adams is one of the best professors Iâ€™ve had. She simplifies complex topics and makes the course engaging.

reviews.subject: Digital Logic Design
reviews.review: Scott's lectures are solid, but the pacing can be a bit fast. You need to stay on top of the material to succeed.

reviews.subject: Computer Graphics
reviews.review: Dr. Lewis is great at explaining difficult topics. The course can be challenging, but his teaching style makes it manageable.

reviews.subject: Operating Systems II
reviews.review: Reed's class is informative but can be tough to follow at times. The workload is reasonable, but the exams are difficult.

reviews.subject: Quantum Computing
reviews.review: Dr. King is a quantum computing expert. Her lectures are fascinating and she makes the material accessible to everyone.

reviews.subject: Data Visualization
reviews.review: Young is a good instructor with a focus on practical skills. The projects are interesting, but sometimes the instructions are unclear.
